<hr size=1> And in those moments where life is still and sullen,<br>
Therein exists a fragment of eternity lying within our grasps.<br>
If life can last forever<br>
Let this be the one.<br>
<br>
I can make myself stronger if you’ll only let me try.<br>
<br>
Pain and love and hope and hate;<br>
They’re all a part of me now.<br>
And I don’t want,<br>
I don’t need,<br>
An existence apart from my own fears and trepidations.<br>
<br>
I touch stars<br>
And their blaze, like a summer on Mercury,<br>
Burns off my past-scarred soul<br>
And renders me anew.<br>
<br>
But, alas, this previous hope and dream is my folly<br>
And will return to haunt me someday.<br>
<br>
Let that day come,<br>
Let that day last forever.<br>
<br>
Pain and love and hope and hate;<br>
They’re all a part of me now.<br>
And I don’t want,<br>
I don’t need,<br>
An existence apart from my own fears and trepidations<br>
<br>
----------------------------------------<br>
